  "edge_hypothesis": "RSI pullback works because price reverts to trend after temporary overextension. Current ACCEPT uses RSI<40 (PF=1.442 at 8:1). Hypothesis: deeper pullbacks (RSI<30 for longs, RSI>70 for shorts) indicate stronger exhaustion and produce more explosive snap-backs. The stricter filter reduces trade count but increases average winner quality. Combined with wide TP to capture the full reversion swing.",
